                "name": "Surface-Bound",
                "text": "A living graffiti can move only along flat surfaces such as floors and walls. If the surface it\u2019s on is destroyed (such as a portrait hit by a <a aonid=\"119\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>fireball</i></a> spell or a puddle being splashed), the graffiti takes 2d6 damage and is shunted to the nearest flat surface. If there is no flat surface within 5 feet, the living graffiti is destroyed."
